INDIAN spinal surgery experts from Spine Clinic are expected in the coun- try this week where they will conduct a screening camp for all patients with spine problems like neck pain, spine pain and sci- atica problems. According to a statement from Regency Medical Centre in Dar es Salaam where the two- day camp will be held on December 19-20, the specialists also will screen various spinal cord problems requiring surgical intervention. The statement says the two-day camp is conducted in the spirit of public private partnership (PPP) of the government and to reduce overseas medical referrals to save the country’s forex. It says the camp is conducted by Regency Medical Centre in collab- oration with Lions Cub of Dar es Salaam (the host). The statement notes that experts will do con- sultation on neck pain, back pain spinal surgical procedures, spinal cord problems and during this camp they will also select patients for major and minor spinal surgical procedures at Regency Medical Centre. “This spinal screen- ing and spinal surgical procedure camp will take place on December 19- 20 at Regency Medical Centre. This is a golden opportunity for fellow Tanzanians to utilise this opportunity of getting treatment, including sur- gical procedures at door steps of Regency Medical Centre in Dar es Salaam,” the statement says.